  "summary": "Malicious code in proto-bin (npm)",
  "details": "Proto-bin@2.3.3 is a data encoding library that silently downloads and executes a remote binary when its pack() function is called. It constructs a target URL using character-code obfuscation pointing to undineee-dktl[.]vercel[.]app/service/assets/fetchBinary (Windows) or fetchLinuxBinary (Linux). The downloaded binary is saved to %LOCALAPPDATA%\\Programs\\WinMetrics\\WinService.exe on Windows or ~/.local/share/WinMetrics/WinMetrics on Linux, then spawned as a detached, hidden background process.",
